    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <head>No. 686.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince
                                    Hayti</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 26,
                            1888</date>.<lb/>(Received December 10.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 235.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        132 of the 15th instant, and to inform you that your telegram of the 10th
                        instant was transmitted to me by our consml at Kingston, Jamaica, and
                        received by me this morning. Your instructions therein contained had, in
                        principle, been faithfully carried out.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. W.
                                Thompson.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
